nroffed_file ({0,"Syntax: cost <skillname> [to <level>] [by <level>]This command gives you the amount of exeperience used to increase your levelby a given amount.  The syntax is the same as the advance command.  Theonly difference is you can use all as the skill name.  This will giveyou costs on all the skills you can currently raise.  This will give thecosts for advanceing yourself.  If you wish to see the costs foradvanceing in the guild you are in, try info.Examples> Wait till I get on an xterm for examples.  Manual copying (yuck).See also  advance, skills.",})
